text:
There are so-called leaders across this country putting themselves between a woman and her right to choose. 

And now they're threatening to prosecute Americans who exercise their right to cross state lines for reproductive health care.

This is literally crazy. https://t.co/2KdY9lkBWp

States across the country have criminalized care. Congress must act.

text: Today at 2:15pm EST, I’ll be talking about my new bill with @PattyMurray and @SenGillibrand that would protect Americans who travel across state lines to receive safe and legal reproductive care.

text_separated: Today, at, 2:15pm, EST,, I’ll, be, talking, about, my, new, bill, with, @PattyMurray, and, @SenGillibrand, that, would, protect, Americans, who, travel, across, state, lines, to, receive, safe, and, legal, reproductive, care.

text: I introduced legislation to make it crystal clear that it's illegal for anti-choice states to limit travel for abortion services. My bill would let the Attorney General bring civil actions against anyone who tries to punish women who cross state lines for critical care.

text: Today, women across America woke up with fewer rights than their mothers before them. I trust women to make their own choices about their pregnancies, their bodies, and their lives. I’ll never stop fighting for our right to do just that.

Today, anti-choice GOPs blocked passage of legislation to protect women traveling to seek reproductive health care.

The ability for women to seek appropriate health care in states like NM that value a women's right to bodily autonomy is essential.

This will not go unchallenged.

🟣 Abolish the filibuster

🟣 Codify Roe

🟣 Codify right to contraception

text:
I will never pretend I’ve had the lived experience of being a woman who finds herself trapped in a situation with nowhere to turn.

I will, however, fight like hell to make sure every woman has the same right to abortion their mothers & grandmothers had for 50 years.

text:

text:
Nevadans stood strong and voted by a 2-to-1 margin to protect reproductive rights in 1990.

Now, Nevada women are standing strong in the House and in the Senate to protect those rights as Republicans in Congress push for a nationwide abortion ban.

We won’t back down.

text:
This is a dark day in our nation's history and a devastating attack on women’s fundamental rights. The Supreme Court’s decision will have dire consequences for women’s health.

We can't give up. I'll keep fighting in every way I can to restore and protect reproductive freedom.

Now, Nevada women are standing strong in the House and in the Senate to protect those rights as Republicans in Congress push for a nationwide abortion ban.

We won’t back down.

Name: Murray, Patty
text_separated:
If, you, thought, Republicans, couldn’t, get, even, more, extreme, on, abortion—they, just, showed, us, otherwise.

They, blocked, our, effort, to, protect, every, American’s, right, to, travel, across, state, lines, to, get, the, health, care, they, need., Mark, my, words:, we’re, not, backing, down, from, this., https://t.co/nXuIfvB4IC

text: Anyone telling you that there isn’t an effort to prevent women’s right to travel to get an abortion isn’t paying attention—or is trying to mislead you. The bill Senate GOP blocked today would have protected a basic right to travel. That really shouldn’t be controversial. https://t.co/e1Q9ueyrtS

text:

text:
How extreme have Republicans gotten on abortion? They want to throw women in jail for traveling across state lines to get an abortion.

My bill with @SenCortezMasto would prevent states from implementing such radical laws—and makes sure there are consequences if they try.

text: People shouldn’t be thrown in jail for trying to get an abortion—let alone providing one or helping a friend get one—but that’s exactly the future MAGA Republicans want. We can’t stand by as they push to make abortion a crime.

text_separated: People, shouldn’t, be, thrown, in, jail, for, trying, to, get, an, abortion—let, alone, providing, one, or, helping, a, friend, get, one—but, that’s, exactly, the, future, MAGA, Republicans, want., We, can’t, stand, by, as, they, push, to, make, abortion, a, crime.

text:

text:
Some states are willing to do anything to restrict abortion – including outlawing the freedom to cross state lines to access health care.
 
That would be unacceptable and likely unconstitutional, so I’m joining with colleagues to introduce a bill to protect the right to travel.

text:
Senate hearings are turning towards abortion over the next few days.
 
The difficult reality is that we don’t have the votes in the Senate now to codify Roe.
 
But I’m not going to give up on looking for ways to protect access to abortion, birth control, and health care.

text:
On this day in 1919, the Senate passed the 19th Amendment – a monumental step forward for women’s rights.
 
I’m disappointed that 103 years later, the Senate is stalling on both protecting the right to vote and a woman’s right to access abortion.
author: {"entities":{"url":{"urls":[{"start":0,"end":23,"url":"https://t.co/sIM9jRW0rP","expanded_url":"http://warner.senate.gov","display_url":"warner.senate.gov"}]}},"name":"Mark Warner","id":"7429102","protected":false,"profile_image_url":"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1396933851453218819/Cdea8Hw5_normal.jpg","url":"https://t.co/sIM9jRW0rP","verified":true,"public_metrics":{"followers_count":507612,"following_count":22991,"tweet_count":12692,"listed_count":4900},"created_at":"2007-07-12T14:03:33.000Z","description":"U.S. Senator from Virginia. \nChairman, Senate Intel Committee.","username":"MarkWarner","location":"Virginia"}

text:
Protecting life means supporting commonsense gun control. It means capping insulin copays at $35/month. It means voting for funding for COVID vaccines. It means not criminalizing abortion when the mother’s life is in danger. 

This is what I am working towards.

Senate hearings are turning towards abortion over the next few days.
 
The difficult reality is that we don’t have the votes in the Senate now to codify Roe.
 
But I’m not going to give up on looking for ways to protect access to abortion, birth control, and health care.

Fundamental freedoms are at risk.

- Promote patients, providers, & clinics safety & security
- Coordinate Federal efforts to protect reproductive rights & access to health care

text:
This Executive Order will:
- Safeguard access to reproductive health care
- Protect patient privacy & access to accurate information
- Promote patients, providers, & clinics safety & security
- Coordinate Federal efforts to protect reproductive rights & access to health care

text:
For more than 45 years, the Hyde Amendment has ensured that taxpayer dollars are not used to fund abortions.
 
I'm proud to stand with so many of my colleagues in pledging to vote against any legislation that puts Hyde at risk.
